<div class="doc-body">

<!-- COLOR -->
<section class="ds-section" id="color">
  <div class="ds-eyebrow">01 · Color</div>
  <h2><strong>Color</strong> Tokens</h2>
  <p class="token-note">Six tokens cover the entire system. No deviations. <code>--black</code> and <code>--white</code> are warm near-neutrals — never pure #000 or #fff. The only "accent" is structural: <code>--mid</code> for secondary text and muted UI. No teal, gold, purple, red, or any hue.</p>

  <div class="swatch-row">
    <div class="swatch">
      <div class="swatch-chip" style="background:#0d0d0b;"></div>
      <div class="swatch-info">
        <span class="swatch-name">Black</span>
        <span class="swatch-token">--black</span>
        <span class="swatch-hex">#0d0d0b</span>
        <span class="swatch-use">Backgrounds (dark), primary text, buttons, nav (scrolled)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="swatch">
      <div class="swatch-chip" style="background:#f6f5f1; border:1px solid #dddad3;"></div>
      <div class="swatch-info">
        <span class="swatch-name">White</span>
        <span class="swatch-token">--white</span>
        <span class="swatch-hex">#f6f5f1</span>
        <span class="swatch-use">Primary section background, button text on dark</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="swatch">
      <div class="swatch-chip" style="background:#efede8;"></div>
      <div class="swatch-info">
        <span class="swatch-name">Off-white</span>
        <span class="swatch-token">--off</span>
        <span class="swatch-hex">#efede8</span>
        <span class="swatch-use">Alternating sections, praise strip, arch strip, table rows</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="swatch">
      <div class="swatch-chip" style="background:#888680;"></div>
      <div class="swatch-info">
        <span class="swatch-name">Mid</span>
        <span class="swatch-token">--mid</span>
        <span class="swatch-hex">#888680</span>
        <span class="swatch-use">Eyebrows, captions, secondary labels, metadata</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="swatch">
      <div class="swatch-chip" style="background:#dddad3;"></div>
      <div class="swatch-info">
        <span class="swatch-name">Rule</span>
        <span class="swatch-token">--rule</span>
        <span class="swatch-hex">#dddad3</span>
        <span class="swatch-use">Dividers, borders, table rules, grid gaps</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="swatch">
      <div class="swatch-chip" style="background:#1e1e1c;"></div>
      <div class="swatch-info">
        <span class="swatch-name">Ink</span>
        <span class="swatch-token">--ink</span>
        <span class="swatch-hex">#1e1e1c</span>
        <span class="swatch-use">Body text on light backgrounds</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <table class="usage-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Token</th><th>Never use for</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>--black</td><td>Pure black replacements — this is warm-dark, not neutral</td></tr>
      <tr><td>--white</td><td>Document backgrounds in print — use #ffffff there only</td></tr>
      <tr><td>--rule</td><td>Text, buttons, or anything requiring contrast</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Any unlisted color</td><td>Do not introduce any new colors without direction</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<!-- TYPOGRAPHY -->
<section class="ds-section" id="type">
  <div class="ds-eyebrow">02 · Typography</div>
  <h2><strong>Type</strong> System</h2>
  <p class="token-note">Two fonts only: <strong>EB Garamond</strong> (display, headings, pull quotes, stat numbers — never uppercase, never h2/h3 in all-caps) and <strong>Outfit</strong> (body, eyebrows, buttons, labels, captions — the only font used uppercase). No third font is ever introduced.</p>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">H1 · EB Garamond 400 · clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 4.2rem) · tracking –0.02em</div>
    <div style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif; font-size:clamp(2.4rem,5vw,4.2rem); font-weight:400; letter-spacing:-0.02em; line-height:1.1; color:var(--black);">Enterprise Strategy at Scale</div>
    <div class="type-note">Used for: page H1s, hero headlines</div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">H1 Italic · EB Garamond 400 italic · clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 4.2rem)</div>
    <div style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif; font-size:clamp(2.4rem,5vw,4.2rem); font-weight:400; font-style:italic; letter-spacing:-0.02em; line-height:1.1; color:var(--mid);">The work behind the work.</div>
    <div class="type-note">Used for: italic H1 variants, hero subtitles. Class: <code>.garamond-italic</code></div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">H2 · EB Garamond 400 · clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.8rem) · tracking –0.02em</div>
    <div style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif; font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.8rem); font-weight:400; letter-spacing:-0.02em; line-height:1.1; color:var(--black);">How I Led the Transformation</div>
    <div class="type-note">Never uppercase. Never Outfit on section H2s.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">H3 · EB Garamond 400 · clamp(1.3rem, 2vw, 1.75rem)</div>
    <div style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif; font-size:clamp(1.3rem,2vw,1.75rem); font-weight:400; letter-spacing:-0.01em; line-height:1.2; color:var(--black);">Service Architecture & System Design</div>
    <div class="type-note">Never uppercase. EB Garamond only.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">Pull Quote · EB Garamond 500 italic · clamp(2rem, 3.2vw, 3rem)</div>
    <div style="font-family:'EB Garamond',serif; font-size:clamp(2rem,3.2vw,3rem); font-style:italic; font-weight:500; line-height:1.2; color:var(--black); border-left:3px solid var(--black); padding-left:36px;">The system had never had a strategy. We built one in twelve weeks.</div>
    <div class="type-note">Border-left: 3px solid --black. Always italic. Component 2 in library.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">Body · Outfit 300 · 1rem · line-height 1.8</div>
    <div style="font-family:'Outfit',sans-serif; font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:var(--ink);">Enterprise service design at this scale requires more than research fluency — it requires the ability to hold organizational complexity, broker across competing stakeholders, and translate ambiguity into systems that can actually be implemented. That is the work I do.</div>
    <div class="type-note">Default body weight is 300 (light). Never bold body text without reason.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">Eyebrow · Outfit 500 · 9px · tracking 0.28em · uppercase</div>
    <div style="font-family:'Outfit',sans-serif; font-size:9px; font-weight:500; letter-spacing:0.28em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--mid);">How I Worked · Kroger · 2022–2025</div>
    <div class="type-note">The only uppercase text pattern. Outfit only. Never EB Garamond uppercase.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="type-specimen">
    <div class="type-meta">Caption / Meta · Outfit 400 · 0.8125rem · --mid</div>
    <div style="font-family:'Outfit',sans-serif; font-size:0.8125rem; font-weight:400; color:var(--mid); line-height:1.6;">Image caption or supporting note goes here. Used beneath photos, images, and artifact descriptions.</div>
  </div>

